    <item>
      <title>Re: [New feature] Do not crop the original imag...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/novenimagecropper/forum/general/new_feature_do_not_crop_the_original_image_but_an_alias/re_new_feature_do_not_crop_the_original_imag3</link>
      <description>Hello Jerome,&#13;
&#13;
1. in tpl get crop value with js in relation to the original&#13;
2. store these information somewhere ( i did this in the original file name )&#13;
3. create a new imagehandler  which handels a crop filter&#13;
&#13;
[ImageMagick]&#13;
Handler=JacImageManipulationEzImageShellFactory&#13;
&#13;
   This crop filter reads the image information&#13;
    you need a new image alias &#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
[crop_reference]&#13;
Reference=original&#13;
Filters[]&#13;
Filters[]=jacimagemanipulation/crop=&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
this alias you can use to create other aliases&#13;
&#13;
The crop algorithm is in JacImageManipulationEzImageShellFactory and is running every time the image alias is rebuild.&#13;
&#13;
Our solution only works for imagemagick at the moment.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Felix Woldt)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/novenimagecropper/forum/general/new_feature_do_not_crop_the_original_image_but_an_alias/re_new_feature_do_not_crop_the_original_imag3</guid>
