      <title>Re: Issue : new ezcImageFilter wants only integ...</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/novenimagecropper/forum/general/issue_new_ezcimagefilter_wants_only_integer_value/re_issue_new_ezcimagefilter_wants_only_integ</link>
      <description>Hi Sébastien and thanks for your feedback.&#13;
Indeed, &lt;i&gt;ezcImageFilter&lt;/i&gt; only accepts integer values. I casted the posted values (classes/novimgcropserverfunctions.php, lines 121 to 124), but I simply forgot that a ratio is then applied (lines 133 to 136).&#13;
&#13;
This is now fixed in trunk (rev 26). I simply cast &lt;i&gt;ezcImageFilter&lt;/i&gt; params as integer.&#13;
&#13;
About the &lt;i&gt;crop.php&lt;/i&gt; file, it was obsolete because now &lt;b&gt;ezjscore&lt;/b&gt; server functions are used. Obsolete module files has been deleted.&#13;
&#13;
I also updated the zip package to version 1.0.5.&#13;
&#13;
Thank you !&#13;
&#13;
PS : I you have other issues to ask for, please make your post in the &lt;i&gt;issues forum&lt;/i&gt; (http://projects.ez.no/novenimagecropper/forum/issues).</description>
