    <item>
      <title>Issue : new ezcImageFilter wants only integer value</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/novenimagecropper/forum/general/issue_new_ezcimagefilter_wants_only_integer_value</link>
      <description>Hi, &#13;
&#13;
I just install your very great extension but I had an error  &#13;
&lt;code&gt;[ Oct 03 2009 21:14:36 ] [192.168.32.1] NovenImageCropper:&#13;
The value '630.4' that you were trying to assign to setting 'x' is invalid. Allowed values are: int.&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
After some debug,  I have chane two file in my extension : crop.php and in novimgcropserverfunctions.php in crop function &#13;
&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;$filters = array( &#13;
		new ezcImageFilter( &#13;
			'crop',&#13;
			array( &#13;
				'x'			=&gt; intval($xRef),&#13;
				'y'			=&gt; intval($yRef),&#13;
				'width'		=&gt; intval($wRef),&#13;
				'height'	=&gt; intval($hRef)&#13;
			)&#13;
		),&#13;
	);&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
Are you ok with this change ?&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
